Creating a List :

lst = List("items")
lst = []

Add list items:

lst.append(item) # only one item will be added
lst.insert(index,item) # inserts an item at given index
lst.extend(lst) #adds other list to current at the end

Remove List items:

lst.remove(item) #removes first occurence of the element
lst.pop(index) #removes item at the given index
lst.clear() #clears all list elements. empty list is the result
del lst #deletes list

Copying a list:

1) Using assignment operator (=)

this is straigth forward approach and its deep copy, i.e changes in original list will reflect in new list

lst1 = lst2

2)Using the copy() method

this is shallow copy , changes in original list won't affect in new list.


IMP Concepts :

1. List Slicing
2. List Comprehension
